# Delete default workspace

Default jj workspace checkouts are not deletable from `sesh`; only named
workspaces can be deleted.

    :bins jj tmux cat test

> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', 'tmux', 'cat', and 'test' are available.

    :copy tests/fixtures/jjconfig.toml .jjconfig.toml (copied)

    :t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
    :$ jj git init beta (exit: 0)
    :$ jj describe -R beta -m "beta commit" (exit: 0)
    :t new-session -d -s ui "sesh -r beta; cat" (success)
    :t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 120 -y 12 (success)
    :pane ui:0.0
    :settle -d 2s (settled)

Filter to the default workspace repo-only entry. The header should not offer
`C-d` delete.

    :k beta
    :snap "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: beta
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none
   beta                                                                                                                ┃
▌  beta                                     ~/beta                                                                     ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) beta commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh




```

Pressing `C-d` should do nothing.

    :k C-d
    :settle (settled)
    :snap --color "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{8})\b/h"

```terminal
session: beta
  1/3 | [C-r] repo: none
   beta                                                                                                                ┃
▌  beta                                     ~/beta                                                                     ┃
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhhhh
│  (empty) beta commit
◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh




```

![light](delete-default-workspace.md.snap.2.light.svg)
![dark](delete-default-workspace.md.snap.2.dark.svg)

The default checkout and picker session should both remain.

    :$ test -e beta (exit: 0)
    :t has-session -t ui (success)

